<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151266>
    dc:description "FIGURE 41. Map showing the localities of the new species of Newportia from Colombia. Newportia tequendama sp. nov. (star), Newportia anopla sp. nov. (circle) and Newportia florezi sp. nov. (triangle)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151266/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151248>
    dc:description "FIGURES 14–16. Newportia (Newportia) anopla sp. nov. Holotype (ICN.MCh-1207). 15. General habitus. 16. Cephalic plate and anterior segments, dorsal view. 17. Cephalic plate." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151248/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151250>
    dc:description "FIGURES 17–20. Newportia (Newportia) anopla sp. nov. Holotype (ICN.MCh-1207). 17–18. Forcipular coxosternite. 19. Head, anterior view. 20. Cephalic plate. Abbreviations: cp: cephalic plate, cxd: coxosternite depression, ft: first tergite, ps: paramedian suture, ptp: processes of trochanteroprefemur, tr: tarsungulum. Scale bars: 200µm (17, 18, 20); 500µm (19)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151250/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151252>
    dc:description "FIGURES 21–24. Newportia (Newportia) anopla sp. nov. Holotype (ICN.MCh-1207). 21. Tergites 9–11. 22. Tergites 9–11. 23. Tergite of ultimate leg-bearing segment. 24. Sternites 9-11. Abbreviations: en: endosternite, lls: lateral longitudinal suture, ls: lateral suture, os: oblique suture, ps: paramedian suture, pt: pretergite, ut: ultimate tergite." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151252/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151254>
    dc:description "FIGURES 25–27. Newportia (Newportia) anopla sp. nov. Holotype (ICN.MCh-1207). 25. Segment 23, prefemur of ultimate legs, lateral view. 26. Right ultimate leg, ventral view. 27. Prefemur and femur of ultimate legs, lateral view. Abbreviations: cx: coxopleuron, f: femur, p: prefemur, t: tibia, t1: tarsus 1, t2: tarsus 2, us: ultimate sternite, ut: ultimate tergite, vsp: ventral spinous processes of prefemur." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151254/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151256>
    dc:description "FIGURE 28. Habitat of Newportia (Newportia) anopla sp. nov. General aspect of the vegetation of the Andean cloud forest, Tenasucá Nature Reserve." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151256/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

